value.name: Park County, Colorado - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Park County is a county located in the U.S. state of Colorado. As of the 2020 census, the population was 17,390. The county seat is Fairplay. The county was named after the large geographic region known as South Park, which was named by early fur traders and trappers in the area.

value.name: Park County, Wyoming - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Park County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming.As of the 2020 United States Census, the population was 29,624. The county seat is Cody.. Park County is a major tourism destination. The county has over 53 percent of Yellowstone National Park's land area. Many attractions abound, including the Buffalo Bill Historical Center, the Cody Stampede Rodeo, the Ghost Town of Kirwin, and the ...

value.name: Park County Wyoming - Park County Wyoming
value.snippet: Park County was established in 1909, and is home to a majority of Yellowstone National Park. According to the US Census Bureau, the county has a total area of 6,967 square miles. As of the 2020 United States Census, there were 29,624 people, and 12,160 households in the county. The population density was 4.1 inhabitants per square mile.
